HR DATA 

KPIs

Attrition by Department -Pie Chart
Shows the number and percentage of people leaving each department. This shows that most people are leaving from the R&D department 56%.this is more than half (50%) of the people leaving.
No of Employees By Age group

Attrition Rate by Gender and Age group - Donut Chart 
This shows that From age 25 and above to over 55, a higher percentage of males leave the job than females.

Education field wise Attrition Stacked Bar Chart
shows the Field where most employees leave, Life Sciences takes the day.

Page 2
Attrition by Marital Status -Line graph
Single people quit more from work and Divorced people are the least likely to quit. For all the Marital Statuses, the males quit more than the ladies 


Attrition Level Based on Travel Frequency.
Those who do not travel at all do not have a high attrition rate. Employees who travel rarely have a high quitting level, with the males quitting more than females 
